HEADWORD: Cyclosis
<hw>Cy*clo"sis</hw> <pr>(s?-kl?"s?s)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL.,
fr. Gr. <grk>ky`klwsis</grk> circulation, from <grk>kykloy^n</grk>. See
<er>Cyclone</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>The circulation or
movement of protoplasmic granules within a living vegetable
cell.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

